long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: After upgrade from F23 to F25 mate-panel applet menus are not localized anymore.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): mate-panel-1.16.0-2.fc25.x86_64
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Log in into mate desktop with locale ru_RU.utf8 2. Have mate-panel with some applets. Mine are Workspace Switcher, Window List, Notification Area, Clock. 3. Press right mouse button on any applet to access its context menu.
Actual results: All menu items are in English.
Expected results: All menu items are localized (Russian, in my case).
Additional info: In the meantime, the context menu of the panel itself is localized.

I guess you're using lightdm and switched the language there? I can confirm that some applets use the system language and not what is set for a user. Fire up system-config-language and change system language to ru_RU.utf8 and restart the system. With new login all is in russian language, see my screenshot.

Btw. i see the same problem also with other languages. If i choose english with system-config-language but my native language german with lightdm, than contextmenus are in english. Not sure which component causes the issue. Lightdm which do not setup all applications in a user session or mate-panel which reads partial the system language.
That's not a solution. I would like to keep English as a system language.
